# Testing Rules

## What to run

```powershell
npm run verify            # before every push: lint + typecheck + unit tests
npm run test:unit         # unit tests only (fast, no DB)
npm run test:integration  # integration tests (needs Postgres in Docker)
npx playwright test       # E2E smoke tests
```

## Test types and locations

- **Unit (Vitest)**: `packages/backend/src/services/__tests__/` and `packages/frontend/src/**/__tests__/`. No DB, no HTTP.
- **Integration (Vitest + supertest)**: `packages/backend/src/__tests__/`. Use a real Postgres instance. Each test file creates its own uniquely-named data and cleans up after itself (time-scoped or unique IDs — never rely on shared seed data for assertions).
- **E2E (Playwright)**: `e2e/`. Runs against the built app. Upload traces and test-results as artifacts on CI failure.

## What to cover

- All service functions (recurrence expansion, gap computation, badge evaluator, coverage detection, notification idempotency).
- Auth flows: login, logout, password reset, role enforcement.
- Event CRUD + state machine transitions.
- Badge catalog: assert >= 100 active definitions, unique keys, valid icons.
- i18n completeness: all cs keys exist in en and vice versa.
- Report aggregations.

## When to add tests

- Bug fix → add a regression test covering the exact case.
- New service function → add unit test.
- New route → add integration test covering happy path + main error cases.
- Do not leave `TODO: add test` comments; add the test or create a task.

## Coverage

- Backend services: minimum 80% line coverage enforced in CI.
- Frontend: ui component snapshot tests are optional; hook/logic tests required.
